killed by police."

00:13:42.760 --> 00:13:44.610
How do you know she was armed?

00:13:44.610 --> 00:13:46.240
Was there some video?

00:13:46.240 --> 00:13:48.870
It's just basically
the police statement

00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:52.040
that they built the
headline off of.

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:55.500
So this is the kind of
practice that we have to end.

00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:57.640
This is the kind of
practice that news outlets

00:13:57.640 --> 00:13:59.870
have to stop doing right now.

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:01.150
I don't think it's fatigue.

00:14:01.150 --> 00:14:01.810
I really don't.

00:14:01.810 --> 00:14:03.970
I think it's racism.

00:14:03.970 --> 00:14:05.770
And I think that
they've been reporting

00:14:05.770 --> 00:14:07.420
like this from the gate.

00:14:07.420 --> 00:14:09.470
This is not new.

00:14:09.470 --> 00:14:10.840
So that's where we're at.

00:14:10.840 --> 00:14:13.840
We need to directly
confront any outlet that

00:14:13.840 --> 00:14:16.180
has an editorial role.

00:14:16.180 --> 00:14:17.800
And that's not just news media.

00:14:17.800 --> 00:14:20.860
That's also social media and
other kinds of technology

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:23.890
companies that curate that--

00:14:23.890 --> 00:14:26.420
WILSON WHITE: So let me
stay there for a second,

00:14:26.420 --> 00:14:28.060
because I'm still
processing this.

00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:30.960
And I saw the news of
the Seattle incident

00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:33.390
yesterday when that came
across the wire as well.

00:14:33.390 --> 00:14:35.210
So this is still top of mind.

00:14:35.210 --> 00:14:39.860
So as a lawyer, I know there's
Supreme Court precedent,

00:14:39.860 --> 00:14:41.360
at least in this
country, in the US,

00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:45.225
that gives law enforcement
significantly--

00:14:45.225 --> 00:14:47.080
I think the standard
is something

00:14:47.080 --> 00:14:51.260
like law enforcement officers
can discharge by standard force

00:14:51.260 --> 00:14:56.350
if they believe or have a
fear that the suspect poses

00:14:56.350 --> 00:14:57.400
a threat to them.

00:14:57.400 --> 00:15:00.444
So even if that threat
is that this person is

00:15:00.444 --> 00:15:01.860
going to charge
them with a first,

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:04.220
they can discharge their
weapon and kill the person,

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:05.170
almost with impunity.

00:15:05.170 --> 00:15:09.190
And that's kind of written
into a Supreme Court precedent,

00:15:09.190 --> 00:15:13.350
which, as you know-- and that's
kind of what you stated here--

00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:17.860
by having that fear be
part of the legal standard,

00:15:17.860 --> 00:15:25.240
it almost bakes in that racial
bias into the legal standard.

00:15:25.240 --> 00:15:27.040
So from an organizing
standpoint,

00:15:27.040 --> 00:15:30.520
because you are an
organizer, what can or should

00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:32.890
we be doing to try to put
pressure on the system

00:15:32.890 --> 00:15:34.800
to change that legal standard?

00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:36.531
Which, I think,
in a lot of ways,

00:15:36.531 --> 00:15:38.280
is the reason why we
don't see convictions

00:15:38.280 --> 00:15:39.280
in these types of cases.

00:15:39.280 --> 00:15:41.200
MALKIA CYRIL: I think
that's a great question.

00:15:41.200 --> 00:15:43.270
And I don't think anyone
has a very clear answer,

00:15:43.270 --> 00:15:44.470
to be honest.

00:15:44.470 --> 00:15:46.090
I think that,
first of all, let's

00:15:46.090 --> 00:15:48.630
