trying to speak for ourselves,

00:21:30.170 --> 00:21:31.595
to plead our own cause.

00:21:31.595 --> 00:21:33.470
And that's what we're
trying to do right now.

00:21:33.470 --> 00:21:40.230
Now, there are some
who profit from the--

00:21:40.230 --> 00:21:43.080
let me say this thoughtfully.

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:47.530
There are black organizations,
Latino organizations,

00:21:47.530 --> 00:21:51.780
Asian organizations,
who have decided

00:21:51.780 --> 00:21:57.832
that the only way to and to--

00:21:57.832 --> 00:22:01.290
I want to be real thoughtful
about how I speak here.

00:22:01.290 --> 00:22:07.500
But that the only way to make
their money and be sustainable

00:22:07.500 --> 00:22:11.636
is to partner with
telecommunications companies.

00:22:11.636 --> 00:22:16.150
Now, the thing is that if you've
been alive for the last 10

00:22:16.150 --> 00:22:19.970
years, you also know that
those same organizations are

00:22:19.970 --> 00:22:21.820
fading in significance.

00:22:21.820 --> 00:22:25.900
That a generation is
emerging that wants

00:22:25.900 --> 00:22:28.810
more than a partnership
with the same companies that

00:22:28.810 --> 00:22:31.600
are denying them mortgages.

00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:33.730
We don't want to just
partner with Wells Fargo.

00:22:33.730 --> 00:22:38.050
We don't want to simply march
in parades with the Homeland

00:22:38.050 --> 00:22:39.070
Security.

00:22:39.070 --> 00:22:41.990
That's why we protest
at gay pride parades.

00:22:41.990 --> 00:22:43.660
