00:22:43.660 --> 00:22:45.775
I'm like, not that kind
of gay-- born black.

00:22:45.775 --> 00:22:47.305
You know what I'm saying?

00:22:47.305 --> 00:22:48.180
You know what I mean?

00:22:48.180 --> 00:22:51.040
That's why we protest,
because it's not--

00:22:51.040 --> 00:22:54.610
we're not interested
anymore in receiving

00:22:54.610 --> 00:22:57.929
their handouts in order
for us to get our freedom,

00:22:57.929 --> 00:22:59.470
because it won't
lead to our freedom.

00:22:59.470 --> 00:23:04.690
So net neutrality for me
is not only an opportunity

00:23:04.690 --> 00:23:08.770
to divest from that
kind of corporate power.

00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:13.840
It's also an opportunity
to invest in black speech,

00:23:13.840 --> 00:23:17.670
in black-- in a different kind
of black power, 21st century

00:23:17.670 --> 00:23:21.260
black power that allows
us to not only speak

00:23:21.260 --> 00:23:24.411
freely, but create our black
businesses that we create

00:23:24.411 --> 00:23:24.910
online.

00:23:24.910 --> 00:23:27.855
When people talk about
Black Twitter, it's like--

00:23:27.855 --> 00:23:28.690
I hate that.

00:23:28.690 --> 00:23:32.320
Because you're giving all the
love to Twitter, but black

00:23:32.320 --> 00:23:36.520
is the part that is making it
interesting and profitable.

00:23:36.520 --> 00:23:40.280
And it's the content
creators that are--

00:23:40.280 --> 00:23:42.255
they might speak on Twitter.

00:23:42.255 --> 00:23:43.570
But actually, they're bloggers.

00:23:43.570 --> 00:23:46.030
And they have
their own websites,

00:23:46.030 --> 00:23:49.150
you know what I'm saying, that
create all of this content that

00:23:49.150 --> 00:23:52.730
then becomes the--

00:23:52.730 --> 00:23:54.700
